          "text": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a77c********9aae</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>tool********76Fg</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-llame/a8b08149-66dc-4dc6-94b9-fa9c75f96110/tasks/a77c4ab6fb1bb9aae.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Research multi-user RBAC schemas\" finished</summary>\n<note>A task-notification fires each time this agent stops with no live background children of its own. The user can send it another message and resume it, so the same task-id may notify more than once.</note>\n<result>## Findings: multi-user identity/groups/membership modeling in self-hosted AI platforms\n\n### 1. Open WebUI (`~/.cache/checkouts/github.com/open-webui/open-webui`)\n\n**User/role** — `backend/open_webui/models/users.py`: single `user` table, `role: Column(String, default='pending')` — a plain string enum (`pending` / `user` / `admin` seen in code), one global role per user account. No per-membership role field.\n\n**Groups** — `backend/open_webui/models/groups.py`:\n- `group` table: `id, user_id (owner), name, description, data(JSON), meta(JSON), permissions(JSON), created_at, updated_at`. No `parent_id` — **groups are flat, do not nest**.\n- `group_member` is a **separate join table**: `id, group_id (FK→group.id, CASCADE), user_id, created_at, updated_at` — not a JSON array on the group row.\n\n**Resource access control** — two generations coexist:\n- Legacy: an `access_control` JSON blob per resource (`{read: {group_ids, user_ids}, write: {...}}`, `None` = public read, `{}` = private).\n- Current (`models/access_grants.py`): normalized `access_grant` table — `resource_type` (knowledge/model/prompt/tool/note/channel/file), `resource_id`, `principal_type` (`\"user\"` or `\"group\"`), `principal_id` (or `\"*\"` wildcard = public), `permission` (`read`/`write`), unique-constrained on the 5-tuple. Conversion helpers (`access_control_to_grants` / `grants_to_access_control`) exist for back-compat.